ce:section.ce:para:
The TEM images of the GQDs-TMNPs (TMNPs = RhNPs, PtNPs, RuNPs) show that the nanocatalysts are of homodisperse (Fig. 1
                        ). It is attributed to the functional groups of GQDs (–OH, –COOH, –CO, etc.), which not only making the GQDs keep excellent hydrophilicity, but also play a stabilizing role by connecting with the surface of TMNPs. The average sizes of GQDs-RhNPs, GQDs-PtNPs, GQDs-RuNPs were measured to be 1.96 nm, 2.56 nm, 2.25 nm, respectively. Then, the high resolution transmission electron microscopy (HRTEM) observation of GQDs-RhNPs shows that the lattice spaces of Rh (111) is 0.221 nm, and the lattice spaces of GQDs (101) is 0.204 nm (Fig. S1). In addition, The EDS spectrum also supported the presence of RhNPs and GQDs (Fig. 2
                        ), it's clear that the RhNPs are connected with the surface of GQDs to form GQDs-RhNPs.
